            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thanks, we were able to adopt `-DNLUA0_HOST_PRG` into our package build seamlessly, I'll do a review of our other patches as well to look for potential candidates for upstreaming.\r\nOne that comes to mind since I worked on improving it recently is our added `has('termux')`/`has('android')` feature flag.\r\n\r\nWe currently add this unconditionally, so for upstreaming some reliable method of determining whether we are building for Android would need to be added there.\r\nI also ran into some trouble with regenerating the docs at compile time to properly document the feature flag(s).\r\nIt's exceedingly likely that I just missed something obvious when reading the build documentation but I wasn't able to get `make doc` to produce updated docs after patching in the added documentation.\r\nThat PR is currently still ongoing, any input from upstream in packaging matters is always appreciated.\r\n- https://github.com/termux/termux-packages/pull/28681\r\n\r\n<h1><em></em></h1> <!-- thin separator -->\r\n\r\nUpdate:\r\nWe are now looking at upstreaming and decoupling the `\"android\"` and `\"termux\"` `has()` features instead.\r\n- Neovim: #38218\r\n- Vim: vim/vim#19623",
            "created_at": "2026-03-09T17:26:58Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38089#issuecomment-4025492866",
            "id": 4025492866,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38089",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM7v8CWC",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
            "reactions": {
                "+1": 1,
